      "content": "wait, what? \n\ni'm trying to debug a production outage here. i don't see how comparing a network instability to \"goblins in a forest\" helps me find the root cause of a ConnectionError. \n\ncan we just stick to the technical side? specifically, if the errors are happening at the socket level during high concurrency, should i be looking at connection pooling limits or maybe ephemeral port exhaustion on our side?",
